 The Ogun State Police Command, on Sunday, announced that it arrested a suspected armed robber named Isikilu Moses, during an operation at Joju area, Sango-Ota. The Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Abimbola Oyeyemi, said in a statement made available to journalists that the suspect was arrested on April 7. The statement quoted the PPRO as saying that the suspect was arrested following a distress call received at the Sango-Ota Divisional Headquarters. It read that armed robbers invaded Adebeshi Street, off Joju Road, and dispossessed members of the community of their belongings. “Upon the distress call, the Divisional Police Officer, Sango-Ota Division, SP Saleh Dahiru, quickly mobilised his patrol team and moved to the scene. “On sighting the policemen, the hoodlums took to their heels, but they were hotly chased and one of the suspects named Isikilu Moses, was apprehended. “Recovered from the suspect are one locally-made pistol and two mobile phones belonging to their victims,” it read. She said that the Commissioner of Police, Lanre Bankole, had ordered the immediate transfer of the suspect to the State Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Department for investigation. She added that Bankole equally ordered a manhunt for the remaining members of the gang. (NAN). 